%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22DOGE%20could%20be%20forced%20to%20release%20its%20records%20under%20a%20new%20court%20ruling%20that%20highlights%20the%20group's%20'unusual%20secrecy'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223837%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Workers%20and%20supporters%20protest%20against%20the%20Department%20of%20Government%20Efficiency%20(DOGE)%20in%20front%20of%20the%20U.S.%20Department%20of%20Labor%20(DOL).%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67cfc6b069253ccddf98d58b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222558%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDOGE%20has%20taken%20numerous%20actions%20to%20slash%20federal%20spending%20since%20Trump%20came%20into%20power%20in%20January.%3Cp%3EAl%20Drago%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDOGE%20has%20been%20ordered%20to%20release%20some%20records%20by%20US%20District%20Judge%20Christopher%20Cooper.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20wrote%20in%20a%2037-page%20opinion%20memorandum%20that%20DOGE%20was%20operating%20rapidly%20but%20with%20%26quot%3Bunusual%20secrecy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe's%20now%20instructed%20the%20agency%20to%20comply%20with%20FOIA%20requests%20from%20a%20watchdog%20nonprofit.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20federal%20judge%20has%20ordered%20Elon%20Musk's%20Department%20of%20Government%20Efficiency%20to%20release%20some%20of%20its%20records%20publicly%2C%20citing%20its%20%26quot%3Bunprecedented%26quot%3B%20authority%20and%20the%20%26quot%3Bunusual%20secrecy%26quot%3B%20with%20which%20it%20operates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20District%20Judge%20Christopher%20Cooper%20instructed%20DOGE%20to%20comply%20with%20a%20nonprofit's%20three%20Freedom%20of%20Information%20Act%20requests%20for%20details%20about%20its%20role%20in%20%26quot%3Bspearheading%20the%20mass%20firings%20and%20dramatic%20disruptions%20to%20federal%20programs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%2037-page%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fecf.dcd.uscourts.gov%2Fcgi-bin%2Fshow_public_doc%3F2025cv0511-18%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eopinion%20memorandum%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Monday%2C%20Cooper%20wrote%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bpublic%20would%20be%20irreparably%20harmed%20by%20an%20indefinite%20delay%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20FOIA%20request.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20DOGE%20to%20deliver%20the%20requested%20information%20quickly%20and%20%26quot%3Bbegin%20producing%20documents%20on%20a%20rolling%20basis%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECooper's%20decision%20is%20the%20first%20major%20legal%20ruling%20that%20has%20sought%20to%20pry%20open%20DOGE's%20operations%20for%20the%20public.%20His%20memo%20mainly%20cited%20news%20reports%20and%20social%20media%20statements%20from%20Musk%20and%20President%20Donald%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20ruling%20can%20be%20appealed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20note%2C%20Cooper%20wrote%20that%20DOGE's%20actions%20%26quot%3Bdemonstrate%20its%20substantial%20authority%20over%20vast%20swaths%20of%20the%20federal%20government.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20wrote%20that%20DOGE%20appeared%20to%20have%20access%20to%20much%20of%20the%20government's%20IT%20systems%2C%20allowing%20it%20to%20act%20and%20move%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20the%20rapid%20pace%20of%20USDS's%20actions%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20requires%20the%20quick%20release%20of%20information%20about%20its%20structure%20and%20activities%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%2C%20citing%20DOGE's%20former%20name%2C%20the%20US%20Digital%20Service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20Trump%20took%20office%20in%20January%2C%20DOGE's%20mandate%20has%20been%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-department-of-government-efficiency%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eax%20government%20spending%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20name%20of%20efficiency.%20As%20part%20of%20that%20effort%2C%20it's%20canceled%20most%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarco-rubio-announces-official-end-of-most-usaid-pr