0leading%20to%20severe%20malnutrition%20and%20anorexia.%20Weighing%20just%2024%20kg%2C%20she%20was%20admitted%20to%20the%20ICU%20but%20did%20not%20recover.%20Anorexia%20nervosa%2C%20a%20serious%20eating%20disorder%2C%20causes%20extreme%20weight%20loss%20and%20serious%20health%20complications.%20The%20condition%20requires%20urgent%20medical%20and%20psychological%20intervention.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20LIFESTYLE%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Flife-style%2Fhealth-fitness%2Fhealth-news%2Fkerala-teen-on-this-diet-dies-of-anorexia%2Farticleshow%2F118876235.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Trump's%20Approach%20To%20Indian%20Tariffs%20Reeks%20Of%20Bullying%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EUS%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20is%20on%20a%20roll%20after%20his%20re-election%2C%20which%20he%20believes%20amounted%20to%20a%20validation%20of%20his%20thinking%20and%20policies%20on%20the%20entire%20gamut%20of%20US%20domestic%20and%20foreign%20affairs.%20Internally%2C%20the%20Democrats%20are%20in%20disarray%20after%20the%20election%20loss.%20With%20both%20the%20House%20and%20the%20Senate%20under%20Republican%20control%20and%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20packed%20by%20Trump%20nominees%2C%20the%20system%20of%20checks%20and%20balances%20in%20the%20US%20political%20system%20has%20become%20weaker%20for%20the%20time%20being.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20slogan%20of%20%E2%80%98Make%20America%20Great%20Again'%20has%20an%20in-built%20contradiction.%20The%20slogan%20has%20domestic%20resonance%2C%20specifically%20in%20the%20context%20of%20an%20economic%20redressal%2C%20of%20rebuilding%20America's%20manufacturing%20base%2C%20US%20companies%20investing%20more%20at%20home%2C%20creating%20more%20jobs%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20The%20slogan%20appeals%20to%20the%20middle%20class%20in%20particular.%20However%2C%20the%20question%20remains%2C%20why%20does%20he%20think%20that%20America%2C%20still%20the%20foremost%20economic%2C%20technology%20and%20military%20power%2C%20is%20not%20great%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20Is%20America%20Not%20'Great'%20Yet%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20leitmotif%20is%20that%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20has%20taken%20advantage%20of%20US%20generosity%20and%20openness%20and%20that%20this%20is%20no%20longer%20acceptable.%20He%20projects%20a%20sense%20of%20victimhood%2C%20whereas%20many%20non-Western%20countries%20see%20themselves%20as%20victims%20of%20the%20US%20power%20over%20the%20years.%20The%20long%20list%20of%20US%20military%20interventions%2C%20overthrow%20of%20governments%2C%20regime%20change%20policies%2C%20the%20weaponisation%20of%20the%20US%20dollar%20and%20US%20control%20over%20the%20global%20financial%20system%2C%20and%20the%20use%20of%20sanctions%20as%20a%20tool%20of%20foreign%20policy%2C%20constitute%20the%20reality%20of%20US%20power.%20Does%2C%20therefore%2C%20the%20vision%20of%20%E2%80%98Making%20America%20Great%20Again'%20have%20overtones%20of%20imperialism%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20%E2%80%9CGreat%20Again%E2%80%9D%20ambition%20includes%20claiming%20Greenland%20for%20national%20security%20reasons%20to%20counter%20Russia's%20domination%20of%20the%20Arctic%2C%20the%20Panama%20Canal%20to%20counter%20China's%20control%20of%20its%20ports%2C%20re-naming%20the%20Gulf%20of%20Mexico%20as%20the%20Gulf%20of%20America%20to%20make%20it%20sound%20less%20Mexican%20and%20more%20American%2C%20repudiating%20Canadian%20sovereignty%20by%20inviting%20it%20to%20become%20the%2051st%20of%20the%20US%2C%20and%20so%20on.%3Cbr%3E%5CnThis%20imperial%20mindset%20leads%20to%20inflicting%20blows%20on%20an%20already%20debilitated%20multilateralism%20by%20withdrawing%20from%20the%20Paris%20Climate%20Change%20Agreement%2C%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%20(WHO)%20and%20the%20UN%20Human%20Rights%20Commission%20(UNHRC).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETariffs%20As%20Currency%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20key%20component%20of%20Make%20America%20Great%20Again%20through%20muscle-flexing%20is%20using%20tariffs%20as%20a%20currency%20of%20power.%20Trump%20believes%20that%20the%20US%20has%20been%20treated%20most%20unfairly%20by%20other%20countries%2C%20and%20this%20includes%20friends%20and%20foes%20alike%2C%20by%20raising%20high%20tariff%20walls%20against%20imports%20from%20America%20while%20exporting%20liberally%20to%20it%20given%20its%20low%20tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20announced%20the%20imposition%20of%2025%25%20tariffs%20on%20imports%20for%20Mexico%20and%20Canada%2C%20with%20whom%20the%20US%20trade%20deficit%20is%20huge.%20He%20has%20not%20treated%20the%20issue%20of%20tariffs%20on%20them%20only%20as%20a%20trade-related%20one%20but%20also%20as%20a%20point%20of%20pressure%20to%20compel%20both%20Mexico%20and%20Canada%20to%20curb%20illegal%20immigration%20and%20the%20trafficking%20of%20the%20drug%20Fentanyl%20into%20the%20US.%20Trump%20has%20suspended%20the%20imposition%20of%20tariffs%20on%20Mexico%20twice%20in%20view%20of%20its%20willingness%20to%20cooperate.%20He%20has%20also%20partially%20suspended%20some%20tariffs%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Canada.%20Trump%20is%20of%20course%20violating%20the%20US-Mexico-Canada%20Free%20Trade%20Agreement%20by%20imposing%20these%20tariffs%2C%20but%20this%20seems%20to%20be%20of%20little%20concern%20to%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20President%20had%20already%20imposed%20a%2010%25%20tariff%20on%20Chinese%20exports%20and%20recently%20announced%20an%20additional%2010%25%20duty.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20China%20too%2C%20he%20has%20sought%20cooperation%20to%20control%20the%20flow%20of%20precursor%20chemicals%20to%20Mexico%20and%20Canada%20for%20the%20production%20of%20Fentanyl%2C%20of%20which%20China%20is%20the%20biggest%20source.%20China%20has%20retaliated%20with%20tariffs%20of%20its%20own%2C%20especially%20on%20US%20agricultural%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20not%20so%20far%20imposed%20tariffs%20on%20EU%20exports%20to%20the%20US%2C%20though%20in%20his%20State%20of%20the%20Union%20Address%2C%20he%20mentioned%20the%20EU%2C%20China%2C%20Brazil%2C%20India%2C%20Mexico%20and%20Canada%20as%20countries%20that%20unfairly%20used%20tariffs%20against%20the%20US%20and%20that%20now%20it%20was%20America's%20turn%20to%20use%20tariffs%20against%20them.%20He%20added%20that%20India%20charged%20100%25%20tariffs%20on%20US%20auto%20exports%2C%20that%20China's%20average%20tariff%20on%20US%20products%20was%20twice%20what%20the%20US%20charged%20them%2C%20and%20that%20South%20Korea's%20average%20tariff%20was%20four%20times%20higher%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20US%20provided%20so%20much%20help%20to%20it%20militarily%20and%20otherwise.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFlawed%20Logic%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20reasoning%2C%20however%2C%20is%20entirely%20flawed.%20India's%20tariff%20structure%20is%20not%20US-specific%2C%20though%20it%20may%20affect%20the%20exports%20of%20some%20US%20products%20to%20the%20country.%20India's%20tariffs%20are%20entirely%20compliant%20with%20World%20Trade%20Organization%20(WTO)%20rules.%20India%20and%20the%20US%20have%20had%20trade%20disputes%2C%20and%20these%20have%20been%20subjected%20to%20the%20WTO's%20Dispute%20Settlement%20Mechanism%2C%20until%20the%20US%20made%20this%20route%20dysfunctional%20by%20opposing%20its%20Appellate%20Body%2C%20blocking%20appointments%20to%20it%2C%20and%20raising%20concerns%20about%20its%20judicial%20independence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20WTO%20rules%20explicitly%20allow%20for%20%E2%80%9Cspecial%20and%20differential%20treatment%E2%80%9D%20of%20developing%20countries%20by%20developed%20countries%2C%20which%20gives%20them%20more%20flexibility%20to%20adapt%20to%20global%20trade%20rules%20based%20on%20their%20development%20level.%20It%20is%20worth%20recalling%20that%20to%20bring%20major%20reforms%20in%20the%20international%20trading%20system%2C%20the%20WTO%20launched%20the%20Doha%20Round%20of%20negotiations%20(billed%20as%20the%20Development%20Round)%20in%202001%20with%20a%20view%20to%20putting%20the%20development%20of%20developing%20countries%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20trade%20negotiations%2C%20with%20special%20and%20differential%20treatment%20for%20developing%20countries%20at%20its%20core.%20Unfortunately%2C%20the%20Doha%20Round%20finally%20collapsed%20in%202011%20because%20of%20opposition%20by%20developed%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20important%20to%20recall%20India's%20position%20during%20these%20failed%20negotiations%2C%20as%20it%20has%20a%20bearing%20on%20our%20interests%20even%20as%20we%20are%20faced%20with%20Trump's%20tariff%20onslaught%20and%20trade%20demands.%20India%20supported%20the%20Special%20Safeguard%20Mechanism%20(SSM)%20to%20protect%20its%20farmers%20from%20import%20surges.%20India%20wanted%20rich%20countries%20to%20drastically%20reduce%20their%20%E2%80%98trade-distorting%20'farm%20subsidies.%20It%20wanted%20a%20permanent%20solution%20to%20the%20issue%20of%20public%20food%20stockholding%20in%20developing%20countries%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20food%20security.%20India%20also%20opposed%20the%20expansion%20of%20the%20multilateral%20trading%20system%20by%20negotiating%20and%20implementing%20multilateral%20agreements%20on%20investment%2C%20competition%20policy%2C%20government%20procurement%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Key%20Disparity%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVery%20simplistically%20and%20unfairly%2C%20Trump%20seeks%20equality%20of%20treatment%20between%20the%20US%20and%20India%20in%20the%20matter%20of%20trade%2C%20rejecting%20the%20concept%20of%20special%20and%20differential%20treatment.%20As%20a%20%2430.4%20trillion%20economy%20and%20a%20per%20capita%20income%20of%20%2488%2C000%20compared%20to%20India's%20nearly%20%244%20trillion%20economy%20and%20a%20per%20capita%20income%20of%20about%20%242%2C700%2C%20the%20US%20and%20Indian%20economies%20are%20far%20from%20being%20equal.%20This%20disparity%20does%20not%20take%20into%20account%20America's%20technological%20strength%2C%20the%20capital%20at%20its%20disposal%2C%20the%20power%20of%20its%20multinationals%2C%20the%20status%20of%20the%20American%20dollar%20as%20the%20global%20reserve%20currency%2C%20and%20the%20capacity%20of%20the%20US%20to%20weaponise%20it%20and%20the%20global%20financial%20system%20as%20a%20result%2C%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20said%20and%20done%2C%20the%20issue%20now%20is%20not%20one%20of%20arguments%20but%20of%20finding%20a%20practical%20way%20forward%20for%20us.%20The%20US%20has%20now%20emerged%20as%20India's%20biggest%20economic%20partner%20in%20goods%20and%20services%2C%20the%20biggest%20investor%2C%20the%20biggest%20source%20of%20modern%20technology%2C%20and%20also%20a%20major%20defence%20partner.%20The%20India-US%20relationship%20has%20to%20be%20managed%20in%20this%20new%20context.%20Faced%20with%20a%20mercurial%20president%20who%20does%20not%20spare%20even%20US%20allies%2C%20India%20has%20had%20to%20show%20some%20nimbleness%20in%20addressing%20Trump's%20repeated%20description%20of%20it%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98tariff%20king'%2C%20of%20not%20giving%20US%20access%20to%20its%20market%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20Even%20during%20the%20joint%20press%20conference%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20during%20his%20otherwise%20rather%20successful%20February%202025%20visit%20to%20Washington%2C%20Trump%20was%20quite%20brutal%20in%20his%20remarks%20about%20India's%20tariffs.%20He%20simplified%20the%20issue%20to%20a%20certain%20level%20of%20absurdity%20by%20stating%20that%20the%20problem%20of%20Indian%20tariffs%20had%20an%20easy%20solution%2C%20because%20the%20US%20would%20impose%20matching%20tariffs%20on%20Indian%20exports%20under%20the%20principle%20of%20strict%20reciprocity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Simplistic%20Approach%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20already%20made%20it%20known%20that%20he%20has%20instructed%20his%20Commerce%20and%20Treasury%20Secretaries%20as%20well%20as%20the%20United%20States%20Trade%20Representative%20(USTR)%20to%20make%20a%20detailed%20study%20of%20not%20only%20the%20tariff%20structures%20of%20countries%20with%20which%20the%20US%20has%20a%20high%20trade%20deficit%2C%20but%20also%20non-tariff%20barriers%2C%20currency%20and%20regulatory%20issues%2C%20etc.%2C%20which%20impede%20trade.%20Trump%20wants%20to%20precipitate%20matters%2C%20disregarding%20the%20complexity%20of%20the%20issues%20involved.%20India%20and%20the%20US%2C%20for%20example%2C%20do%20not%20have%20the%20same%20export%20baskets%20in%20their%20trade%20with%20each%20other.%20How%20would%20strict%20reciprocity%20be%20implemented%3F%20If%20the%20average%20tariff%20on%20US%20exports%20to%20India%20is%20about%2015%25%20and%20that%20on%20Indian%20exports%20to%20the%20US%20is%20a%20little%20over%203%25%2C%20how%20will%20this%20reciprocity%20be%20fine-tuned%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20had%20already%20done%20extensive%20homework%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20tariffs%20before%20Modi's%20US%20visit%2C%20during%20which%20conversations%20were%20also%20held%20with%20US%20Commerce%20Secretary%20Howard%20Lutnick%20and%20USTR%20Jamieson%20Greer.%20India's%20strategy%20is%20to%20address%20the%20issue%20through%20a%20multi-sectoral%20bilateral%20trade%20agreement%20with%20the%20US%2C%20the%20first%20tranche%20of%20which%20would%20be%20concluded%20by%20the%20autumn%20of%20this%20year%2C%20when%20Trump%20is%20expected%20to%20visit%20India%20for%20a%20Quad%20summit.%20This%20figures%20in%20the%20joint%20statement%20issued%20on%20the%20occasion%20of%20Modi's%20visit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWaiting%20For%20April%202%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20quick%20follow-up%2C%20keeping%20in%20mind%20Trump's%20declaration%20that%20on%20April%202%20he%20will%20be%20announcing%20the%20imposition%20of%20tariffs%20on%20various%20countries%2C%20India%20had%20already%20signalled%20its%20willingness%20to%20address%20the%20issue%20of%20tariffs%20by%20announcing%20in%20the%20annual%20budget%20the%20lowering%20of%20some%20duties%20on%20products%20of%20interest%20to%20the%20US.%20This%20was%20noted%20in%20the%20joint%20statement.%20India%20seems%20ready%20to%20make%20a%20success%20of%20the%20negotiations%20on%20tariffs%2C%20given%20the%20stakes%20involved%2C%20although%20agriculture%20will%20be%20a%20very%20sensitive%20issue%20for%20it.%20Commerce%20Minister%20Piyush%20Goyal%20recently%20visited%20the%20US%20for%20talks%20with%20Lutnick%20and%20Greer%2C%20with%20a%20message%20of%20India's%20readiness%20to%20lower%20tariffs%20to%20expand%20India-US%20trade%20both%20ways.%20Trump%2C%20always%20eager%20to%20claim%20success%20in%20%E2%80%9Cdeal-making%E2%80%9D%2C%20has%20already%20announced%2C%20based%20on%20his%20feedback%20from%20Goyal's%20talks%2C%20that%20India%20will%20be%20lowering%20tariffs%20on%20US%20goods.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet's%20see%20what%20Trump%20announces%20on%20April%202.%20He%20has%20India%20on%20his%20mind%2C%20but%20given%20our%20anticipatory%20moves%20and%20Trump's%20changeability%2C%20it%20can%20be%20hoped%20that%20he%20will%20not%20announce%20tariffs%20that%20might%20make%20the%20negotiations%20on%20the%20envisaged%20multi-sector%20trade%20agreement%20more%20complicated.%20No%20country%20likes%20to%20negotiate%20under%20duress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Kanwal%20Sibal%20was%20Foreign%20Secretary%20and%20Ambassador%20to%20Turkey%2C%20Egypt%2C%20France%20and%20Russia%2C%20and%20Deputy%20Chief%20Of%20Mission%20in%20Washington.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741672920000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2Fqlsfm4r_trump-afp_625x300_05_March_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fcan-trump-really-announce-more-india-tariffs-next-month-7897268%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Very%20simplistically%20and%2