third%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20India%20saw%20a%207%20per%20cent%20decline%20in%20PM2.5%20concentrations%20in%202024%2C%20averaging%2050.6%20micrograms%20per%20cubic%20metre%2C%20compared%20to%2054.4%20micrograms%20per%20cubic%20metre%20in%202023.%20Yet%2C%20six%20of%20the%20world's%2010%20most%20polluted%20cities%20are%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelhi%20recorded%20consistently%20high%20pollution%20levels%2C%20with%20an%20annual%20average%20PM2.5%20concentration%20of%2091.6%20micrograms%20per%20cubic%20metre%2C%20nearly%20unchanged%20from%2092.7%20micrograms%20per%20cubic%20metre%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2013%20Indian%20cities%20in%20the%20world's%20top%2020%20most%20polluted%20cities%20are%20Byrnihat%2C%20Delhi%2C%20Mullanpur%20(Punjab)%2C%20Faridabad%2C%20Loni%2C%20New%20Delhi%2C%20Gurugram%2C%20Ganganagar%2C%20Greater%20Noida%2C%20Bhiwadi%2C%20Muzaffarnagar%2C%20Hanumangarh%20and%20Noida.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%2035%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20Indian%20cities%20reported%20annual%20PM2.5%20levels%20exceeding%2010%20times%20the%20WHO%20limit%20of%205%20micrograms%20per%20cubic%20metre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAir%20pollution%20remains%20a%20serious%20health%20risk%20in%20India%2C%20reducing%20life%20expectancy%20by%20an%20estimated%205.2%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20Lancet%20Planetary%20Health%20study%20published%20last%20year%2C%20about%201.5%20million%20deaths%20in%20India%20every%20year%20from%202009%20to%202019%20were%20potentially%20linked%20to%20long-term%20exposure%20to%20PM2.5%20pollution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPM2.5%20refers%20to%20tiny%20air%20pollution%20particles%20smaller%20than%202.5%20microns%2C%20which%20can%20enter%20the%20lungs%20and%20bloodstream%2C%20leading%20to%20breathing%20problems%2C%20heart%20disease%20and%20even%20cancer.%20Sources%20include%20vehicle%20exhaust%2C%20industrial%20emissions%20and%20the%20burning%20of%20wood%20or%20crop%20waste.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20WHO%20chief%20scientist%20and%20health%20ministry%20advisor%20Soumya%20Swaminathan%20said%20India%20has%20made%20progress%20in%20air%20quality%20data%20collection%20but%20lacks%20sufficient%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20the%20data%3B%20now%20we%20need%20action.%20Some%20solutions%20are%20easy%20like%20replacing%20biomass%20with%20LPG.%20India%20already%20has%20a%20scheme%20for%20this%2C%20but%20we%20must%20further%20subsidize%20additional%20cylinders.%20The%20first%20cylinder%20is%20free%2C%20but%20the%20poorest%20families%2C%20especially%20women%2C%20should%20receive%20higher%20subsidies.%20This%20will%20improve%20their%20health%20and%20reduce%20outdoor%20air%20pollution%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20PTI%20in%20an%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20cities%2C%20expanding%20public%20transport%20and%20imposing%20fines%20on%20certain%20cars%20could%20help.%20%26quot%3BA%20mix%20of%20incentives%20and%20penalties%20is%20necessary%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFinally%2C%20strict%20enforcement%20of%20emission%20laws%20is%20crucial.%20Industries%20and%20construction%20sites%20must%20comply%20with%20regulations%20and%20install%20equipment%20to%20cut%20emissions%20instead%20of%20taking%20shortcuts%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20former%20director%20general%20of%20the%20Indian%20Council%20of%20Medical%20Research%20added.%20PTI%20GVS%20AS%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741660620000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-01%2F360geuuo_delhi-pollution_625x300_03_January_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fworlds-20-most-polluted-cities-13-of-worlds-20-most-polluted-cities-in-india-delhi-most-polluted-capital-7895690%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Thirteen%20of%20the%20world's%20top%2020%20most%20polluted%20c